HIGH PRESSURE ACROSS NE SCANDINAVIA AMPLIFIES A RIDGE SW INTO THE N SEA
THIS INTERACTING WITH ICELANDIC LOW PRESSURE TO BRING A SWATHE OF NEAR GALE
OR GALE FORCE WINDS ACROSS FAIR ISLE THROUGH FRIDAY NIGHT. MEANWHILE A WKN
FRONTAL TROUGH TRACKS E ACROSS THE IRISH SEA AND SERN UK AND A RIDGE BUILDS
N TO THE W OF IRELAND. THIS SECOND RIDGE SOON DECLINES ON SATURDAY AS A DEEPER
LOW DEVELOPS TO THE S OF ICELAND AND PUSHES A FRONTAL TROUGH E ACROSS MUCH
OF PORTPATRICK WITH A SHALLOW LOW DEVELOPING TO THE S OF IRELAND LATER. THIS
LOW TRACKS AWAY ACROSS BISCAY ON SUNDAY ALLOWING HIGH PRESSURE TO STRETCH
FM THE AZORES ACROSS CENTRAL UK TO SCANDINAVIA BUT DEEP AREAS OF LOW PRESSURE
